headline: Cummins (CMI): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Cummins’s 28.9% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 12.8%, and its stock price has climbed to $426.90 per share. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
